50|$|After {{these rules}} were issued, {{advances}} in terrain mapping technology permitted {{the development of}} a new type of <b>ground</b> proximity <b>warning</b> <b>system</b> that provides greater situational awareness for flight crews. The FAA has approved certain installations of this type of equipment, known as the enhanced <b>ground</b> proximity <b>warning</b> <b>system</b> (EGPWS). However, in the proposed final rule, the FAA is using the broader term “terrain awareness and warning system” (TAWS) because the FAA expects that a variety of systems may be developed in the near future that would meet the improved standards contained in the proposed final rule.|$|R
