2500|$|At 1810:24 the <b>ground</b> {{proximity}} <b>warning</b> <b>system</b> (GPWS) {{began to}} sound a [...] "sink rate" [...] warning in the cockpit. The aircraft was descending {{at an angle}} of 7 degrees, when the angle of descent for most aircraft landing on that runway was 3 or 4 degrees. Both pilots ignored the warnings. [...] At 1810:44 the <b>warning</b> <b>system</b> in the cockpit began to sound. The captain responded to these warnings with [...] "that's all right." ...|$|R
