50|$|On {{the night}} of the accident, Flight 2415 was {{operated}} using a BAe Jetstream 31 twin-turboprop airliner, registration number N410UE. The aircraft was manufactured in October 1987, and had accumulated approximately 4,972 flight hours {{at the time of the}} accident. The aircraft was not equipped with a <b>ground</b> proximity <b>warning</b> <b>system</b> and did not have a cockpit voice recorder or flight data recorder.|$|R
